oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Real Photo postcard of German 77mm cannon
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: This photograph has "German 77mm captured by Americans near Chery Cheatures (?) August 1918" inscribed on the reverse. This was one of the most common field guns used by the Germans in WWI and variants of it continued to be used by other countries into WWII.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: World War, 1914-1918; World War, 1914-1918 - History
